{"dataset":"articles","provider":"pursuit","banner_url":"data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mNkYAAAAAYAAjCB0C8AAAAASUVORK5CYII=","id":"73919","text":"<div data-component=\"HeroVideoBlock\" ><div class=\"container\" data-v-4bbde884><div class=\"row\" data-v-4bbde884><div class=\"col-12\" data-v-4bbde884><figure class=\"ps-figure ps-figure--full-width\" data-v-4bbde884><div class=\"ps-embed-video__wrapper\" data-v-4bbde884><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/vHYUpsu5Lfs?autoplay=1&amp;rel=0\" id=\"vidlink\" class=\"ps-embed-video__link\" data-v-4bbde884><div class=\"ps-embed-video\" style=\"max-width:845px;max-height:480px;\" data-v-4bbde884><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mNkYAAAAAYAAjCB0C8AAAAASUVORK5CYII=\" alt style=\"background-image:url(https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vHYUpsu5Lfs/maxresdefault.jpg?&amp;enablejsapi=1);max-width:845px;max-height:480px;\" data-v-4bbde884><div class=\"ps-embed-video__play-button\" data-v-4bbde884><svg id=\"playButtonSVG\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"   viewBox=\"0 0 128 128\" fill=\"none\"><rect id=\"playButtonRect\"   rx=\"64\" fill=\"black\"></rect><path id=\"playButtonPath\" d=\"M42.666 100.934V26.2676L101.333 63.6009L42.666 100.934ZM50.666 86.4009L86.5327 63.6009L50.666 40.8009V86.4009Z\"></path></svg></div><div class=\"ps-embed-video__video-title\" style=\"display:none;\" data-v-4bbde884><span class=\"ps-embed-video__title\" data-v-4bbde884></span><span class=\"ps-embed-video__duration\" data-v-4bbde884></span></div></div><div class=\"ps-embed-video__iframe-wrapper\" style=\"display:none;\" data-v-4bbde884><iframe class=\"\" src   frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay\" allowfullscreen id=\"widget2\" title=\"Augmented Reality: Getting under the skin\" data-v-4bbde884></iframe></div></a></div><figcaption class=\"ps-figure__caption\" data-v-4bbde884>WATCH: A team of University of Melbourne ocean engineers is working with Australian and international researchers to develop an autonomous, multi-camera monitoring system for measuring different properties of the ocean surface. Video: University of Melbourne</figcaption></figure></div></div></div></div><span><p>Our team is now designing an even more comprehensive monitoring system in collaboration with the <a href=\"https://www.antarctica.gov.au/\" target=\"_self\">Australian Antarctic Division</a>, <a href=\"https://www.csiro.au/en/research/natural-environment/oceans/the-antarctic\" target=\"_self\">CSIRO</a> and national and international partners as part of an Australian Research Council <a href=\"https://dataportal.arc.gov.au/RGS/Web/Grants/LE220100103\" target=\"_self\">Linkage Infrastructure, Equipment and Facilities (LIEF) project</a>.</p><p>In addition to stereo and infrared cameras, the new system has a bow camera for taking pictures of the ice as it’s broken up by the ship’s progress – letting us calculate the ice thickness.</p><p>We’ll also add cameras that record in the near-infrared range, so we can study what’s on the ice surface, like snow, water and even organic matter like algae.</p></span><!--[--><!--noindex--><article class=\"ps-cta container\" data-component=\"CallToAction\" data-v-1d83364b><div class=\"ps-cta__flex\" data-v-1d83364b><div data-v-1d83364b><img src=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0026/73961/varieties/375w.jpg\" data-v-1d83364b></div></div><div class=\"ps-cta__info\" data-v-1d83364b><div class=\"ps-cta__top\" data-v-1d83364b><p class=\"ps-cta__channel ps-ff-source-sans-pro ps-fw-semibold ps-text-uppercase\" data-v-1d83364b>Environment</p></div><a class=\"ps-cta__link ps-ff-source-sans-pro ps-fw-semibold ps-lh-120 ps-cta__black\" href=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/articles/cop28-is-a-global-stocktake-of-climate-change?in_c=in_article_cta\" target=\"_self\" data-v-1d83364b><p data-v-1d83364b>COP28 is a global stocktake of climate change <i class=\"ps-icon--arrow-right ps-cta__black\" data-v-1d83364b></i></p></a></div></article><!--endnoindex--><!--]--><span><p>Anything that covers the ice can affect how much solar radiation is absorbed or reflected, so these substances have an important role in the heat exchange between the ocean and atmosphere, which contributes to the Earth’s weather and climate.</p><p>The monitoring system will also be integrated with the ship’s meteorological station, providing data on wind, humidity and other basic atmospheric parameters.</p><p>The new system will be installed in December on the new Australian icebreaker <a href=\"https://www.antarctica.gov.au/nuyina/\" target=\"_self\">RSV Nuyina</a> to monitor the Southern Ocean and marginal ice zone during its resupply expeditions.</p><p>Occasionally, part of the equipment will be moved to the <a href=\"https://mnf.csiro.au/en/RV-Investigator\" target=\"_self\">RV Investigator</a>, CSIRO’s research vessel, to monitor sections of the Pacific and Indian oceans in the lower latitudes.</p></span><div class=\"container\" data-v-012796f8><figure class=\"ps-figure\" data-v-012796f8><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"ps-figure__image\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" srcset=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0025/73924/varieties/64w.jpg 64w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0025/73924/varieties/160w.jpg 160w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0025/73924/varieties/375w.jpg 375w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0025/73924/varieties/768w.jpg 768w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0025/73924/varieties/960w.jpg 960w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0025/73924/varieties/1280w.jpg 1280w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0025/73924/varieties/1440w.jpg 1440w,https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0025/73924/varieties/1920w.jpg 1920w\" src=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/__data/assets/image/0025/73924/adee6a0076ca02c15bd8b2d06a2f7bd97bc53601.jpg\" alt   data-v-012796f8><figcaption class=\"ps-figure__caption\" data-v-012796f8>The monitoring system uses off-the-shelf equipment fitted onto icebreaking ships. Picture: Supplied </figcaption></figure></div><span><p>We will build a comprehensive database of wave and sea ice properties in the Southern Ocean, which will be integrated with other atmospheric data.</p><p>This much-needed resource will be crucial not only for validating data from satellite-based remote sensing but also for advancing climate model capabilities so we can better understand future climate change scenarios.</p><p>Banner: Pancake ice in the marginal ice zone of the southern ocean.</p><p><span class=\"italics\">Pictures and videos supplied by Professor Alessandro Toffoli</span></p></span>\n<p>This article was first published on <a href=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au\">Pursuit</a>. <a href=\"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/articles/the-southern-ocean-is-earth-s-climate-engine-room\">Read the original article.</a></p>","date_published":"2023-12-05T11:34:52+11:00","date_updated":"2023-12-05T11:34:52+11:00","url":"https://pursuit.unimelb.edu.au/articles/the-southern-ocean-is-earth-s-climate-engine-room","title":"The Southern Ocean is Earth’s climate ‘engine room’","summary":"A shipboard monitoring system is giving researchers much-needed measurements of Antarctic wind, waves and ice","org_objects":[],"tag_objects":[],"author_objects":[{"name":"Professor Alessandro Toffoli","url":"https:\\/\\/pursuit.unimelb.edu.au\\/individuals\\/professor-alessandro-toffoli","orcid":"","fae_url":"https://findanexpert.unimelb.edu.au/profile/771507-alessandro-toffoli","email":""}],"citation_objects":[{"credentials":"Professor Alessandro Toffoli"}]}